this tutorial as much as needed.

00:00:25.470 --> 00:00:26.470
To be best prepared to replace the Power Supply
Unit (PSU) Board inside of your TV, you will

00:00:26.470 --> 00:00:27.470
need the following materials:
A pair of latex gloves.

00:00:27.470 --> 00:00:28.470
Your ShopJimmy.com replacement Power Supply
Unit (PSU) Board.

00:00:28.470 --> 00:00:29.470
A pair of needle-nose pliers.

00:00:29.470 --> 00:00:30.470
Both a flat-head and phillips screwdriver.

00:00:30.470 --> 00:00:31.470
And a cup to hold all screws, clips, and any
other small items.

00:00:31.470 --> 00:00:32.470
So let's get to it shall we?

00:00:32.470 --> 00:00:34.500
Locate your TVs identification label and take
note of the brand name model number, serial

00:00:34.500 --> 00:00:38.840
number and model code if present.

00:00:38.840 --> 00:00:43.490
Unscrew and remove the back cover.

00:00:43.490 --> 00:00:46.410
The LCD Integrated Power Supply (LIPS) Board
contains the Power Supply Unit (PSU) and Backlight

00:00:46.410 --> 00:00:48.670
Inverters (BLI).

00:00:48.670 --> 00:00:51.610
For this TV, the LCD Integrated Power Supply
(LIPS) Board is located at the left side of

00:00:51.610 --> 00:00:53.960
the chassis.

00:00:53.960 --> 00:01:02.190
Carefully unplug all wires by hand.

00:01:02.190 --> 00:01:07.560
Unlock the wire connectors by squeezing the
tab or tabs and gently remove the wires.

00:01:07.560 --> 00:01:13.080
Be sure to keep a firm grip with both hands.

00:01:13.080 --> 00:01:17.210
Unscrew and remove your bad Power Supply Unit
(PSU) Board.

00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:21.100
Slide the board out of the bulb connectors.

00:01:21.100 --> 00:01:29.369
he part number for this item can be found
printed on a label.

00:01:29.369 --> 00:01:33.020
Search your part number on http://www.shopjimmy.com
to find a compatible replacement.

00:01:33.020 --> 00:01:35.200
Click on the search results to view important
product specifications.

00:01:35.200 --> 00:01:36.200
Some replacement boards are version or TV
specific.

00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:37.200
Please be sure to look on the product page
for notes regarding serial number or part

00:01:37.200 --> 00:01:38.200
number requirements.

00:01:38.200 --> 00:01:40.829
Verify that your original board matches all
requirements noted in the product description

00:01:40.829 --> 00:01:45.039
prior to purchase.

00:01:45.039 --> 00:01:48.719
Slide the board into the bulb connectors.

00:01:48.719 --> 00:01:54.109
Insert all screws to secure your ShopJimmy
New Power Supply Unit (PSU) Board to the chassis.

00:01:54.109 --> 00:02:00.399
Reconnect all cables.

00:02:00.399 --> 00:02:06.149
Return the back cover to its original position
and secure all screws.

00:02:06.149 --> 00:02:09.509
This ShopJimmy replacement Power Supply Unit
(PSU) Board does not require any manual configurations

00:02:09.509 --> 00:02:11.850
in order to function.

00:02:11.850 --> 00:02:15.650
Simply plug in and power on and your TV will
function as if new.

